iciently as starburst galaxies with\nsimilar gas surface densities. \"The fall\" of star formation in these galaxies\nwas not precipitated by complete gas expulsion or redistribution. Rather, this\nhigh-resolution view of PSBs' ISM indicates that star formation in their\nremaining compact gas reservoirs is suppressed by significant turbulent\nheating.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 Aug 2021 17:59:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 10 Mar 2022 18:12:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-04"}
